<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>SSRF Vulnerability Lab</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F2EFEB 0%, #918B83 100%);
            min-height: 100vh;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(48, 44, 42, 0.2);
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3C1053 0%, #B51825 100%);
            color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .header h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 2.5em;
            font-weight: 300;
        }
        .header p {
            margin: 10px 0 0 0;
            opacity: 0.9;
            font-size: 1.1em;
        }
        .content {
            padding: 40px;
        }
        .warning {
            background: #F2120C;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            text-align: center;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .services-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }
        .service-card {
            background: #F2EFEB;
            border: 2px solid #918B83;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }
        .service-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(48, 44, 42, 0.2);
        }
        .service-card h3 {
            color: #3C1053;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .service-card p {
            color: #302C2A;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            background: #3C1053;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background 0.3s ease;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 16px;
        }
        .btn:hover {
            background: #B51825;
        }
        .btn-safe {
            background: #918B83;
        }
        .btn-safe:hover {
            background: #302C2A;
        }
        .info-section {
            background: #F2EFEB;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        .info-section h2 {
            color: #3C1053;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .info-section ul {
            color: #302C2A;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .internal-services {
            background: #302C2A;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .internal-services h3 {
            color: #F2120C;
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .internal-services ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .internal-services li {
            padding: 5px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #918B83;
        }
        .internal-services li:last-child {
            border-bottom: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>üîí SSRF Vulnerability Lab</h1>
            <p>Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) Educational Environment</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="content">
            <div class="warning">
                ‚ö†Ô∏è WARNING: This application contains intentional security vulnerabilities for educational purposes only!
            </div>

            <h2>Available SSRF Attack Vectors</h2>
            <div class="services-grid">
                <div class="service-card">
                    <h3>üåê Basic SSRF</h3>
                    <p>Simple URL parameter injection without validation</p>
                    <a href="/vulnerable" class="btn">Test Basic SSRF</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-card">
                    <h3>üì° Request Library SSRF</h3>
                    <p>SSRF using the request library (different attack vector)</p>
                    <a href="/vulnerable-request" class="btn">Test Request SSRF</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-card">
                    <h3>üìÅ File Protocol SSRF</h3>
                    <p>Local file access through file:// protocol</p>
                    <a href="/vulnerable-file" class="btn">Test File SSRF</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-card">
                    <h3>üîó Gopher Protocol SSRF</h3>
                    <p>Advanced SSRF using gopher:// protocol</p>
                    <a href="/vulnerable-gopher" class="btn">Test Gopher SSRF</a>
                </div>
                
                <div class="service-card">
                    <h3>‚úÖ Safe Implementation</h3>
                    <p>Properly secured endpoint with validation</p>
                    <a href="/safe" class="btn btn-safe">Test Safe Endpoint</a>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-section">
                <h2>üéØ Learning Objectives</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understand how SSRF vulnerabilities occur</li>
                    <li>Learn to identify vulnerable code patterns</li>
                    <li>Practice exploiting different SSRF attack vectors</li>
                    <li>Implement proper input validation and URL filtering</li>
                    <li>Understand the impact of SSRF on internal services</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="internal-services">
                <h3>üè† Simulated Internal Services</h3>
                <p>These services represent internal infrastructure that should be protected:</p>
                <ul>
                    <% Object.entries(internalServices).forEach(([name, service]) => { %>
                        <li><strong><%= name %></strong>: http://localhost:<%= service.port %><%= service.endpoint %></li>
                    <% }); %>
                </ul>
                <p><em>Try accessing these internal services through the vulnerable endpoints!</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
